{"session_id":"svc-1778625229013315765","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-12T22:33:51.024603649Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"codex","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-f7c3d512-20260512T223345-bd0f215b","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Too big if any holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across ~5+ files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;- If the bead description exceeds 8000 bytes, treat Step 0 as a split-first pass.\u0026#xA;- Auto-decomposition is capped at depth 2: root beads may split once, decomposed children once more; third-level splits must be rejected with an explanation.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;`.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260512T223345-bd0f215b/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing child IDs, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a success. Do not mix implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260512T223345-bd0f215b/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;`.ddx/executions/20260512T223345-bd0f215b/no_changes_rationale.txt` must contain one:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;cmd\u0026gt;` — repo cwd; exit 0 closes, nonzero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: open` + `reason: \u0026lt;retryable\u0026gt;` — open, smart retry.\u0026#xA;- `status: proposed` + `reason: \u0026lt;operator needed\u0026gt;` — operator lane.\u0026#xA;- `status: blocked` + `reason: \u0026lt;external blocker\u0026gt;` — blocked lane.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;No pseudo-statuses. Bare rationales and `status: needs_investigation` reject.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;To request orchestrator decomposition, add `orchestrator_action: decompose` alongside `status: open`.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260512T223345-bd0f215b/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260512T223345-bd0f215b/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Mode and overrides\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;DDX_MODE=bead_execution: edit code/docs for bead AC. Only broad queue-steward default is overridden; tracker, merge-policy, verification, safety stay active. Bead description/AC override CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, and project defaults.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Review gate\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- The review is a gate, not an escape hatch — meet every AC in this pass.\u0026#xA;- Address every BLOCKING `\u0026lt;review-findings\u0026gt;` item; do not declare `no_changes` with blocking findings open.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Constraints\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Work only inside this execution worktree.\u0026#xA;- Keep `.ddx/executions/` intact — DDx uses it as execution evidence.\u0026#xA;- **Never run `ddx init`** — the workspace is initialized; running it corrupts the bead queue.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s named scope.\u0026#xA;- Do not rewrite CLAUDE.md, AGENTS.md, or other project-instructions files unless the bead asks.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## When the work is done\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;After the commit succeeds and every AC is verified, stop. Return control to the orchestrator — do not keep exploring or testing.\n  \u003c/instructions\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-f7c3d512\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003ereview: turn dispatcher / harness integration\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;No turn dispatcher exists for review sessions. The review mutations (reviewSessionStart, reviewSessionRespond) have no mechanism to take a ReviewSession + user turn, assemble the review prompt, invoke the reviewer harness, and record the resulting turn. Without this, review sessions produce no AI response.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/server/ contains no ReviewSessionDispatcher or equivalent struct/function.\u0026#xA;- Prompt assembly for review turns does not exist (Step B1b in the review plan: assemble system rubric + artifact content + turn history into a reviewer prompt).\u0026#xA;- The existing dispatch path (execute_bead_loop.go / cli/internal/agent/) invokes harnesses for bead execution, not review; review needs a parallel no-tool dispatch path.\u0026#xA;- ddx-f1e12904 (cost cap + routing, a dep) must land first.\u0026#xA;- No-tool mode: reviewers must not write files. Enforcement varies per harness (claude: disable tool use flag; codex: best-effort; document where not enforceable).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Add cli/internal/server/review_dispatcher.go with DispatchReviewTurn(ctx, session, userTurn):\u0026#xA;  1. Assemble review prompt: system rubric + artifact content + prior turns.\u0026#xA;  2. Invoke reviewer harness via existing dispatch path (no-tool mode).\u0026#xA;  3. Record resulting turn in turns.jsonl.\u0026#xA;- Audit no-tool mode for claude harness (disable tool use) and codex harness (best-effort; document).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- GraphQL schema and mutations (ddx-de278b8d, a dep).\u0026#xA;- Cost cap enforcement (ddx-f1e12904, a dep).\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. DispatchReviewTurn(ctx, session, userTurn) exists in cli/internal/server/review_dispatcher.go.\u0026#xA;2. Turn recorded in .ddx/reviews/\u0026lt;session-id\u0026gt;/turns.jsonl after each dispatch.\u0026#xA;3. No-tool mode confirmed for claude harness (tool use disabled in request).\u0026#xA;4. No-tool mode for codex harness documented as best-effort in source comment.\u0026#xA;5. TestReviewDispatcher_DispatchTurn_RecordsTurn verifies turn appended to turns.jsonl.\u0026#xA;6. TestReviewDispatcher_NoToolMode_ClaudeHarness verifies tool use disabled in claude dispatch.\u0026#xA;7. Integration test: TestReview_FullTurnLifecycle exercises dispatch through recording.\u0026#xA;8. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/server/... green.\u0026#xA;9. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, story:18, area:server, kind:feature, triage:no-changes-unjustified\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-42b917fe\" base-rev=\"c3279ced5b096f767a9b4fd2c37e91e3a0b2604f\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260512T223345-bd0f215b\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n\u003c/execute-bead\u003e\n","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260512T223345-bd0f215b","base_rev":"c3279ced5b096f767a9b4fd2c37e91e3a0b2604f","bead_id":"ddx-f7c3d512","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260512T223345-bd0f215b","correlation_id":"ddx-f7c3d512:20260512T223345-bd0f215b","prompt_file":".ddx/executions/20260512T223345-bd0f215b/prompt.md","prompt_sha":"4437c829fbcda468017543b6df7ce8a5ebc74ad4a3b2f5220a9d69b4c7eccc22","role":"implementer","session_id":"eb-d56bf1ab","worker_id":""}}}
